blog.name: thisislakewood
blog.title: Lakewood, Texas
blog.description:
Lakewood, Texas presents the image of a simple town, a place for people to create a life without the terror that plagues other parts of the world. The illusion was always that it was safe, warmed by a Texan sun and a friendly hello from the commoners that have lived in Lakewood all their lives. But they learned their lesson with the kicking up of dust from a lone biker, to the cartels that moved like packs of coyotes along one another: Lakewood is a death sentence. Those who choose to live here take the responsibility that they might not live to see the sun set the next day. Families in power all want to dominate the town, a prime place for business on the border, while dodging the impending presence of FBI agents in town. Who can trust who? A good versus evil with the underlining tone that everyone is corrupted. Now, only one question remains: which side do you stand on?

Mobile Navigation
Opened since December 2018.

summary: “I find the character so inspiring that whenever I feel nervous and scared, I feel like I can turn to her and I feel like, No, I...
caption: “I find the character so inspiring that whenever I feel nervous and scared, I feel like I can turn to her and I feel like, No, I got this. And that feels really awesome. I feel like I have the same awe over her that a lot of her fans do. I had a meeting with Marvel and what we discussed was they wanted to make a big feminist movie. I remember going home and being like, Shit, am I going to do this?” […] “It’s kind of everything that I’ve wanted. As I’ve grown, I’ve noticed that these movies and the Marvel movies in particular have so much meaning in them. They mean so much. You can have a great time and just enjoy it for having a great time, but you can also be left with some really deep philosophical questions. That combo is really powerful.” […] “The beauty of this is that there’s been so many women involved in the making of it that I don’t feel like I’ve had to fight as much, ‘cause I felt understood from the beginning.” - Brie Larson
